A review of the genus Geraldus Fitton (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae: Banchinae), with description of a new speciesAn undescribed species of Banchinae from Chile in the Natural History Museum collections is described as Geraldus fittoni Broad, sp. nov. Four more specimens of Geraldus cambrensis have been found, from Chile and Argentina. The monophyly of Geraldus and of Philogalleria are supported.